result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy R Lochowicz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Timothy R Lochowicz in court, in custody, with attorney Mark E. Kershek.   Ted S. Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court passes matter for parties to clarify offer.  Case recalled at 3:01.  Prosecuting attorney moves to strike the repeater from Count 1.  Court grants motion.  Repeater struck from Count 1.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2, 3 and 4 dismissed and read in.

Court orders the following:

Count 1:
- Total sentence: 4 years (Initial Confinement: 2 years, Extended Supervision: 2 years) STAYED.  Credit for 73 days if revoked.
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration
- Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- 3 years Probation. 
- Court costs waived
- Restitution of $59.96 to be paid to Walmart as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Attend a minimum of 2 self help meetings per week and continue to have a sponsor.  No contact with Walmart.  No contact with L.B.  Maintain full-time employment and/or school after treatment is well established.
CONDITION TIME: 60 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence FORTHWITH.
